Knightbook Tips

What is the Menlo Knightbook?

The Knightbook is Menlo’s electronic student photo directory, which lets you look up student information. You can easily search students by name and sort by alpha order or class year. When you click on any photo more information, including address and family contacts, will appear. Click on a parent’s name and their contact information will show, and if that parent has a Google profile photo, their photo will even appear!

Searching and Sorting to Customize Your View

Want to see just the senior class? Use the filters at the top to customize your search. Want to see the entire school in alphabetic order? Use the sort by option at the top and select Last Name A-Z.

Knightbook on the Go

For quick access to the Knightbook, bookmark it on all of your devices. You can also pin it to your mobile device’s home screen to launch it like an app. If you are on your cell phone, you can click on the phone number to place a call or the address to open a map of the location.

Finding a Student with a Different Last Name than their Parent

In the top right corner of the Knightbook navigation, click on Parent Directory. Then, you can search for the parent by first or last name. Click on the name of the person you are looking for, which will reveal their contact information as well as the names of their Menlo students. If you click on the student names, it will take you to the student’s Knightbook profile.

Knightbook Shortcuts

  • Export and print: You can export any current view of the Knightbook to PDF to print or save. Just look for the export icon in the upper right corner. You’ll also be able to set the options for what information should be included in the export.
  • Parent photos appear along with parent contact information when an image has been set up in the parent’s Gmail or Google Plus account.
  • Custom lists: You can create custom lists of students, such as friends, classmates, or club/team members. Click the list icon that appears when you hover over a student’s photo and click New List to name your list. Then click the checkbox next to the list name to add the student. Your lists, which are unique to your login, will appear in the filter menu and you can combine them with the other filter options.
  • Learning names mode: There’s a built-in tool to help you learn student names. Click on the light bulb icon in the upper right corner to hide names until you hover over a student photo. You can also opt to shuffle student photos in this mode.

Note: The Knightbook is for Menlo School use only and is not to be used for personal solicitations, mailings, and/or advertising purposes.
